originalText.text:
Good and modern facility. Ideal for Guggenheim museum visitors, Consulate General of Russia, and other points on Madison and 5th Ave, on the Upper East Side area, from mid 80s to mid 90s streets.
Affordable prices, particularly the "early bird specials".

originalText.text: Parked here while visiting the MET Museum in April 2023. The attendant was very polite and kind. I purchased my pass for 9am-9pm just in case we wanted to stay late. He mentioned that if I would have come in before 9 then they would have had to charge more money which was mentioned on the SpotHero site. He asked me an estimated time of when I would be back and then we were off to the museum. When I went to pick up my car around 6 pm, there was a different attendant and I showed him my printed pass. Before I showed it to him, he told me the exact price that was on my pass which was $28.49. I will definitely use this garage again when visiting in the area.

originalText.text: You can tell the employees hate their job. One guy was sooooo rude! He banged on my window door and told me to move my car. It was my first time here. I said “hi good morning” he said how long you staying i said i wasnt sure 30 mins- 1 hr. Then when i came back he had a face on like i did something to him. He told me swipe my card im like this is the price ($29), he didnt answer im like hello? He yells look over there you don’t read everything. I said to him you’re very rude you must hate your job. He says “no im annoyed because people always ask me the same thing all the time and park and block up the place”. You can’t take your frustration out on everyone because of other customers thats your job! You choose to work there. For me being a first time customer i will never return again! Very rude
